Date: Mon, 31 Jul 2000 05:58:37 -0700
From: "M. Cosgriff" <mcosgriff@hotmail.com>
Source: Reuters: Mon, 31 Jul 2000 12:58:37 GM [edited

Encephalitis kills 10 people in Northern India
----------------------------------------------
LUCKNOW: Encephalitis has killed 10 people in the north Indian state of
Uttar Pradesh in the last two days and a dozen patients are being treated,
doctors said on Monday. V.P. Gupta, chief medical superintendent at a local
hospital, said all the victims were from villages in the Bahraich district
which lies near the border with Nepal. "About a dozen more such patients
are currently being treated in the hospital. Most of them are in a critical
condition, but we're trying to do our best to fight the disease," Gupta
told Reuters by telephone. Outbreaks of encephalitis, or swelling of the
brain, are an annual feature in the mosquito-infested region on the Uttar
Pradesh-Nepal border.
